      Text:
        m_Untranslated: 'Right click "Pivot", select "Make Transition" and drag the
          arrow towards "Locomotion". Set the "Exit Time" to 1 and keep the "Transition
          Duration (s)" to something low like 0.05.


          Select the transition
          from "Idle" to "Locomotion" and set the "Interuption Source" to "Next State".
          Also select the transition from "Locomotion" to "Idle" and set the "Interuption
          Source" to "Current State". This will ensure that our "Pivot" state takes
          precedence over our "Idle" state.


          Play now and our character
          will pivot smoothly before returning to walking. The next page adds running
          pivots so you don''t lose your speed when running.




          Toptip:

          It
          is very important that the "Exit Time" is set to 1 so that the pivot completes
          in full, otherwise our character might only turn e.g. 140 degrees when
          we want them to turn 180 degrees.'
